review_blob: Golden colour, nice foamy head. Great combination of hops and malts. Not as flavourfull as other cream ales yet delicious none the less. Definitely worth a try.
One of the worst honey browns I have ever tasted. Tried it once thought it must be skunky, since I had heard good things. Tried it a second time a few months later, still terrible.
Very light and fruity. Typical american macrobrew. I almost wanna say i taste banana. Boring crappy beer best left to the young ones just starting off in the world of beer.
Not bad for a local restaurants house brew. Nice flavour, clean finish. Golden yellow colour. Main flaw, too fizzy.
Bad beer. Frequently ordered by men with mullets who get upset when I tell them we dont have it on tap.
Excellent summer beer. Very light, almost no aftertaste. Careful, the green bottle encourages skunkiness! Get it good and you will be happy, but not blown away.

Great full taste. Smooth finish. Very refreshing, very drinkable. Will only become more popular as time goes on. Draught is preferable but bottled is more than adequate. Perfect for a weekend at the cottage.

Rich roasted flavour, delicious malty goodness. Amazing beer for a macrobrew!
Of course draught is recommended but bottles were surprsingly good.
Smooth, creamy, fantastic head. Rich amber colour. Sweet with a slightly bitter finish.
